<p>Coding protection…  use a clamping function to make sure you limit it while tuning it.  As you get dialed in relax the clamp.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">  public void useOutput(double output, TrapezoidProfile.State setpoint) {

    // Calculate the feedforward from the sepoint
    double feedforward = m_feedforward.calculate(setpoint.position, setpoint.velocity);

    // Add the feedforward to the PID output to get the motor output
    double volts = MathUtil.clamp(output + feedforward, -6.0, 6.0);
    m_motor.setVoltage(volts);
  }
</code></pre>
<p>This based on the WPILIB arm example.</p>
